  <bioghist id="aspace_2d68457e812adf437b53bb9bd3bdb9eb">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>This archive was collected by Dr. Bruce V. Lewenstein, a professor in the Dept. of Communication at Cornell University, Dr. Thomas F. Gieryn of Indiana University, and Dr. William Dougan, and others, with the assistance of the National Science Foundation. They're collecting documented the technical, semi-technical, popularized articles, and written material created in the aftermath of the March 1989 announcement that researchers at two universities in Utah had created nuclear fusion at room temperatures.</p>  </bioghist>
  <userestrict id="aspace_2f0b8d5218c55ea8258aef4a053883d7">
    <head>Restrictions on use:</head>
<p>Taped interviews have individual restrictions. Consult guide.</p>  </userestrict>
  <prefercite id="aspace_64096640864bec3bf4b17346887159d4">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
